mintinstall (8.3.0) wilma; urgency=medium

  [ Michael Webster ]
  * flatpak match data: Add a second entry for steam:i386.
  * Update flatpak match data.

  [ Ulrik de Muelenaere ]
  * Add a setting to filter apt/Flatpak results for the same application, with a fix for search sorting (#398)

  [ Michael Webster ]
  * Add a verified badge for flatpaks from Flathub.
  * Cleanup some files.

  [ Alexander K ]
  * Speed up initialization by optimizing package sorting
  * Initialize application in a thread for a responsive GUI

  [ Michael Webster ]
  * Add script to check category lists for non-existent packages.
  * Update test script to compile settings schemas.
  * Use AppStream instead of AppStreamGlib.
  * Rework search preferences submenu, add header row for search filtering options.
  * Flag unverified Flatpaks, not verified, display developer name when available.
  * Don't call self.on_installer_ready on a thread.
  * Misc. optimizations mainly aimed at startup time.
  * Use a different message in the busy view during startup.
  * Clean up, add some more benchmarking to costly operations.
  * Handle some API breaks between AppStream versions.
  * Add missing icon.
  * Remove a leftover print statement.
  * Use a static image instead of a spinner during app startup.
  * Add a preferences page, move search settings there.
  * Hide unverified Flatpaks by default, discourage them otherwise.
  * When showing installed apps, always show all Flatpaks.

  [ Clement Lefebvre ]
  * Rephrase warnings/badge/tooltips for unverified flatpaks
  * l10n: Update POT
  * l10n: Generate files

  [ Michael Webster ]
  * Try the project_group if developer and developer_name are missing from appdata.

  [ Michael Webster ]
  * apt_flatpak_matcher.py: Write output files after each iteration instead of waiting until the end.
  * Update apt<->flatpak matches.

  [ Corbin Auriti ]
  * Add Banner Slideshow using Gtk.Stack with nice animations (#417)

  [ Michael Webster ]
  * Recognize the new apt steam-installer package.
  * banner: Ignore banner apps with no pkginfo.
  * Overlay the banner dots on the banner's bottom to save space.
  * Don't use symbolic banner dots, override some more css for them.
  * Use https for debian.net screenshot lookups, improve screenshots for deb packages.
  * Reset the screenshot controls when loading a new package.
  * Use the cached 'developer' field instead of relying on appstream.
  * Pause the banner timer when not on the landing page, don't start it until mintinstall is done initializing.
  * Remove the 'steam' package from featured/banner apps, only allow 'steam-installer'

  [ Corbin Auriti ]
  * fix dot click error (#425)

